How will parents benefit from the application?

The application is designed and programmed to predict the value of bilirubin responsible for Jaundice disease in newborns from the age of two to 14 days, and to give recommendations to parents to help them reduce the percentage of Jaundice in newborns. It is considered a simulation of the device used in the hospital.
Are the test results in the app accurate?
The accuracy of the application is excellent and reliable
Yes, the application is free and does not need to pay any money to obtain the examination service or track the status of the newborn.
What are the most important services in the application?

The most important services lie in obtaining the result of the estimated bilirubin level in the newborn, and also the presence of a medical record for the newborn containing the dates of the previous examinations that the newborn had carried out, the percentage of jaundice, and also the recommendations that must be carried out by the parents.
Is the inspection service available at all times?
Yes, as parents can use the application 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, to check their children and check their Jaundice level.
Does the application service include any updates, additional features, or fixing technical problems?
Yes, the application will be developed with new features and characteristics periodically, and your application will be updated automatically when any new feature or feature is added.
Does the application support all operating systems?
The app only supports Android and can be downloaded from the Google play store
